{"title":"Friday Roundup: Trail & Complete Streets for all, Trash Free Trails, Shimano 100th & more!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/26/friday-roundup-trail-complete-streets-for-all-trash-free-trails-shimano-100th-more/","date":1614369669000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><b>Sierra Buttes wants “A Trail for Everyone”</b><b>&nbsp;</b>– The Sierra Buttes Trail Stewardship has&nbsp;launched a short film about Connected Communities, their proposed “Lost Sierra Route” project, and the positive impact of linking 15 California mountain communities together with off-road trails.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YznR3NDwDYc?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" ezoid=\"0.032480762049327705\"></iframe></span></p><p>“<em>The Lost Sierra is a place where many come to be found. To lose themselves in the region’s beauty in order to find something special within themselves. But for those of us that call it home, a more difficult task is at hand: how to survive. We can all benefit from the beauty this region has to offer, and share it with the world in a way that is sustainable for generations.</em>“</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Sierra-Buttes-Trail-Stewardship_A-Trail-for-Everyone_CC-map.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Sierra-Buttes-Trail-Stewardship_A-Trail-for-Everyone_CC-map.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Sierra-Buttes-Trail-Stewardship_