com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Restrap-Orange-Fast-straps_orange-is-the-new-black_bikepacking-luggage-strap-1536x960.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Restrap-Orange-Fast-straps_orange-is-the-new-black_bikepacking-luggage-strap-696x435.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Restrap-Orange-Fast-straps_orange-is-the-new-black_bikepacking-luggage-strap-1068x668.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Restrap-Orange-Fast-straps_orange-is-the-new-black_bikepacking-luggage-strap-672x420.jpg 672w\"></a></p><ul><li><b>Restrap says Orange is the New Black… for straps</b> – UK bag maker Restrap wants you to strap some luggage to your bike and head out on adventure. Their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/30/restrap-bikepacking-bolts-on-top-tube-bag-adds-fast-strap-brompton-handle-hip-pouch-more/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hypalon Fast Straps</a> now come in color-coordinated orange, to secure your bikepacking load… or just an extra jacket, no bags required. Bright orange will make them easier to find in your pack. The straps come in 25cm, 45cm &amp; 65cm lengths starting at £8 / $12, or a set of all three for £16 / $24. You can even get the old black ones if colors scare you. <a href=\"https://restrap.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Restrap.com</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1000\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools.jpg 1300w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-297x228.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-800x615.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-768x591.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-696x535.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-1068x822.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-546x420.jpg 546w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools.jpg 1300w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-297x228.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-800x615.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-768x591.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-696x535.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-1068x822.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Moots-Silca-40th-anniversary-tools-546x420.jpg 546w\"></a></p><ul><li><strong>Get a Moots 40th anniversary edition Silca hex set</strong> – It’s hard to argue with a good set of tools to keep your bikes in tune. And so Moots partnered with their friends at Silca for a commemorative Moots 40th Anniversary version of their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2015/08/12/silca-introduces-the-hx-one-hex-essentials-kit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">premium allen wrench set</a>. Beautifully crafted tools, housed in a CNC machined Beechwood case with magnetic closure, and custom engraved Moots 40th Anniversary logos. Get#em while they last for $145 a set at: <a href=\"https://shop.moots.com/products/moots-40th-anniversary-custom-home-allen-wrench-set-by-silca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Moots.com</a></li></ul><p><span>Industry News &amp; Contest</span></p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/LIujfkyVbqw?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><ul><li><b>Don’t forget about Shimano’s 100th anniversary</b> – We all know that Shimano has something big coming this year to celebrate their centennial. Will it be all-new Dura-Ace? Will it be all-new XTR? How about wireless, 12 or 13 speeds? What we do know is that something is coming in 22 days. In the meantime, you can enter <a href=\"https://www.shimano.com/en/100th/contest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shimano’s year of Photo Contests here</a>, with a shot at winning some “centennial novelty” schwag. Just submit your “<em>Lively Movement</em>” snaps now. Then, follow along for new goodness with us at: <a href=\"https://www.shimano.com/en/100th/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shimano.com/100th</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"500\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads.jpg 700w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-297x212.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-120x86.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-696x497.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-588x420.jpg 588w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-100x70.jpg 100w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads.jpg 700w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-297x212.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-120x86.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-696x497.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-588x420.jpg 588w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Campy-gravel-before-roads-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><ul><li><strong>Take a trip down memory lane with Campagnolo’s gravel origins</strong> – If you are more interested in Italian gruppos, maybe it’s time to dive into Campagnolo’s heritage on gravel roads as part of their #BornBeforeRoads campaign. While Campy built their brand on premium road racing performance, they’ve been doing it so long that all of that early racing was actually gravel road racing. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=ekar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ekar is only their newest name for it</a>. Grand Tours, the heritage Classics, so much of the history of road cycling was actually developed off-road, literally before there were smooth paved roads. <a href=\"https://www.campagnolo.com/WW/en/CampyWorld/Corporate/campagnolo_born_before_roads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Campagnolo.com</a></li></ul></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2468691002112ead110ac1aab348c240f7a1b88d7bafc8f57c917f96450cc822","category":"Cycling"}